main event: A civilian observer reported sighting a bright white round object in Tacoma, Washington on October 23, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for 4.5 minutes, The object had a shape and size resembling a quarter, The object rose to 3-4 degrees above the horizon before it diminished in size, The sighting occurred while the observer was on their front porch, The object emitted no discernible features or trails.
witness description: Civilian observer who noticed the object from their front porch
